50|$|Recourse debt {{can either}} be full or limited {{recourse}} debt. A full recourse debt gives the granter {{the right to take}} any and all assets of the debtor, up to the full amount of the debts. The lender will sell the seized assets, including the asset acquired through the <b>original</b> <b>loan.</b> Limited, or partial recourse debt, relies on the <b>original</b> <b>loan</b> contract, where named assets are {{the extent to which a}} lender may take action.|$|R
